definitions.definition: A very fine starch powder derived from maize ( US corn ) used in cooking as a thickener, to keep things from sticking, or as an anti-caking agent.
A flour for baking and cooking that is ground from maize ( US corn).

main_definition: ( British ) A very fine starch powder derived from maize ( US corn ) used in cooking as a thickener, to keep things from sticking, or as an anti-caking agent.
secondary_definitions: A flour for baking and cooking that is ground from maize ( US corn).
